1
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,440
Thank you.

2
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,080
No matter what,

3
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,279
I am changing Lin Jiaqi little by little.

4
00:01:21,519 --> 00:01:23,279
And I had such a darn bad day today,

5
00:01:24,599 --> 00:01:26,519
yet I didn't expect such a good ending.

6
00:01:32,639 --> 00:01:33,959
I was just saying that.

7
00:01:35,199 --> 00:01:36,120
Don't overthink it.

8
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:38,919
Whether I do or not is my own business.

9
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,879
It doesn't matter even if I'm disappointed.

10
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,760
I said I would wait for you,

11
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:47,800
so I will keep waiting.

12
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:51,239
Even if I have to wait a long time.

13
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,879
Even if it hurts and makes me sad.

14
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:57,360
But this way,

15
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,360
doesn't it also prove that I'm alive?

16
00:02:06,639 --> 00:02:07,080
President Gu

17
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:08,479
Then we'll do this as you wish.

18
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:08,919
Okay.

19
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,639
Wait a moment.

20
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,240
President Gu! President Gu!

21
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,119
Something happened!

22
00:02:16,399 --> 00:02:17,039
Rosenmoss

23
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,279
applied to freeze our accounts.

24
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:19,440
Rosenmoss?

25
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:20,759
On what grounds are they freezing our accounts?

26
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,399
They said they're exercising their creditor's rights.

27
00:02:22,639 --> 00:02:23,720
They do have the right

28
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,759
to freeze our accounts.

29
00:02:26,279 --> 00:02:27,839
Creditor's rights?

30
00:02:30,919 --> 00:02:32,240
It's not just the employees' salaries.

31
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:33,520
Right now, we can't even

32
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:35,080
make payments and do Reconciliation

33
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,279
with our partners.

34
00:02:39,119 --> 00:02:39,639
President Gu.

35
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:41,360
What's wrong?

36
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,080
Something happened at the factory.

37
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:44,800
Wait, wait, wait!

38
00:02:45,119 --> 00:02:45,440
Wait!

39
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,839
I'm contacting the head office right now.

40
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,399
Stop moving things! Stop!

41
00:02:48,399 --> 00:02:49,559
What's the use of contacting them?

42
00:02:50,279 --> 00:02:51,360
With the current situation,

43
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,559
the head office can't do anything either.

44
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:53,320
Move aside!

45
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,240
Don't delay us from moving things.

46
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:54,759
No,

47
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,279
it's useless for you to move them now.

48
00:02:58,279 --> 00:02:58,679
Let's go.

49
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:00,160
We won't be able to get our money back,

50
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,520
but if we take these things,

51
00:03:02,119 --> 00:03:03,639
at least we can make up for some losses.

52
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,119
How much loss can these raw materials cover?

53
00:03:06,199 --> 00:03:08,279
We can only get paid if they become finished products!

54
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,399
Stop fooling us.

55
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,679
Does this factory

56
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:11,639
look like it can

57
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,919
start production?

58
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:13,679
Move them!

59
00:03:14,639 --> 00:03:15,199
Don't panic.

60
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,000
Call Uncle Du immediately.

61
00:03:17,839 --> 00:03:19,360
Tell him to do his best to calm down

62
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,800
the workers at the factory.

63
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:21,880
Okay, I got it.

64
00:03:23,399 --> 00:03:23,880
Jiaqi,

65
00:03:24,119 --> 00:03:25,199
a lot of people came here.

66
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,839
They want to take all the raw materials away.

67
00:03:26,839 --> 00:03:27,600
What should we do?

68
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,679
I'm begging you, please don't move them!

69
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,199
Listen to me, stop moving them!

70
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:32,520
Old Du,

71
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,039
we've known each other for so many years.

72
00:03:35,199 --> 00:03:36,240
Please do us a favor

73
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,440
and stop blocking us.

74
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,720
The factory can't even pay our salaries,

75
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,559
and we have families to feed.

76
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,279
Please be considerate of us.

77
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:44,360
Move them!

78
00:03:44,559 --> 00:03:45,160
Move!

79
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,360
No!

80
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:47,520
Hello?

81
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,279
Jiaqi,

82
00:03:48,279 --> 00:03:49,039
you heard it too.

83
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,080
I can't stop them.

84
00:03:53,559 --> 00:03:54,399
What should we do?

85
00:03:55,399 --> 00:03:56,919
If this continues,

86
00:03:57,119 --> 00:03:58,080
our new products

87
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,199
can't be produced at all.

88
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,360
No,

89
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:02,199
we can't produce the products,

90
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,360
and our funds are frozen.

91
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,679
We're being attacked from all sides.

92
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:05,759
Right now,

93
00:04:05,839 --> 00:04:06,559
we either do wholesale

94
00:04:06,839 --> 00:04:07,520
or resort to loan sharking.

95
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,279
Otherwise, the company will be finished.

96
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,160
Bankruptcy.

97
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:11,880
Don't even think about loan sharking.

98
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:13,960
Not to mention it's illegal,

99
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,519
even the interest of loan sharking

100
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,839
is something we can't afford at all.

101
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,600
Under Gu Tiancheng's loss-making management,

102
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,480
Feimanchi is already on the verge of collapse.

103
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:29,279
Regarding the Reconciliation,

104
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:31,119
hand it over to Director Liu.

105
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:33,880
Let's see what the higher-ups decide.

106
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:41,720
Jiaqi.

107
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,600
You must be exhausted lately.

108
00:04:50,399 --> 00:04:51,200
Thanks to you.

109
00:04:52,119 --> 00:04:53,040
What are you saying?

110
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,799
How could it be thanks to me?

111
00:04:56,359 --> 00:04:57,279
Why did things go wrong

112
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,079
exactly during the reconciliation

113
00:04:59,079 --> 00:04:59,760
with the other party?

114
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,279
I should be asking you that,

115
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,200
Mr. Feng.

116
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,519
Mr. Feng?

117
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,359
You're acting so distant with me now.

118
00:05:07,359 --> 00:05:08,480
Aren't we old friends?

119
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:10,200
Old friends?

120
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,880
You're so capable.

121
00:05:12,239 --> 00:05:13,000
With just a few words and laughs,

122
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,519
a company is wiped out.

123
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,600
How could a nobody like me

124
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,559
ever be friends with you?

125
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,519
You flatter me too much.

126
00:05:21,119 --> 00:05:22,119
I'm not that capable.

127
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,799
Then again,

128
00:05:24,799 --> 00:05:26,200
we've known each other for a long time.

129
00:05:26,799 --> 00:05:27,720
I didn't want to make things

130
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,839
turn out like this either.

131
00:05:30,359 --> 00:05:31,320
But it's the company's request,

132
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:32,839
so I have to get it done.

133
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,720
Seeing Gu Tiancheng at his wit's end,

134
00:05:38,679 --> 00:05:39,519
how does it feel?

135
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,480
How does it feel?

136
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,359
Right now, just like President Gu,

137
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,720
I'm extremely anxious.

138
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,359
Isn't seeing me like this

139
00:05:49,359 --> 00:05:50,519
exactly what you wanted?

140
00:05:51,519 --> 00:05:52,880
You finally got your wish.

141
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:53,760
Jiaqi,

142
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,679
is it worth it?

143
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,679
Whether it's worth it is my business.

144
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,119
I don't need to tell you.

145
00:06:03,359 --> 00:06:04,480
The best part is yet to come.

146
00:06:08,679 --> 00:06:09,320
Jiaqi,

147
00:06:09,839 --> 00:06:10,640
you need to know that

148
00:06:11,119 --> 00:06:11,799
even the proudest person

149
00:06:11,799 --> 00:06:12,760
under certain circumstances

150
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,959
will bow down and grovel.

151
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,679
What kind of person Gu Tiancheng is,

152
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,320
I'll let you see clearly tomorrow.

153
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:25,959
President Gu, take a look.

154
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,279
These are the contact details

155
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:30,880
of some well-known individual investors.

156
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,640
I compiled them when

157
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:34,679
Chairman Gu was still in charge.

158
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:35,880
What do you mean by this?

159
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,760
Change investors.

160
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,000
Although we are short on funds,

161
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:43,839
we have a batch of patents.

162
00:06:44,239 --> 00:06:45,119
Based on this alone,

163
00:06:45,119 --> 00:06:45,920
we still have the confidence

164
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,959
to negotiate with them.

165
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:48,640
Is it your first day at the company?

166
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,239
You know very well

167
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,200
how hard it is to attract investment with just technology.

168
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,720
Plus, we don't have any guarantees.

169
00:06:55,279 --> 00:06:56,160
Relying solely on technology,

170
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,440
how could we possibly attract

171
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,519
massive investments in just one day?

172
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,119
I know that.

173
00:07:01,119 --> 00:07:02,000
I know it's very difficult.

174
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:02,880
But if we don't give it a try,

175
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:03,920
how will we know it won't work?

176
00:07:04,119 --> 00:07:05,839
Even if there's only a one percent chance...

177
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:06,279
But for this matter,

178
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,679
there isn't even a one percent hope.

179
00:07:08,279 --> 00:07:09,320
Are we just going to give up

180
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:10,320
without even trying?

181
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,040
Right now, I really have

182
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,320
a lot of things to worry about.

183
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,160
Stop causing trouble, okay?

184
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,119
I don't want to waste all my time

185
00:07:17,119 --> 00:07:18,600
on these unnecessary things.

186
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:20,920
Aren't you just wasting time sitting here too?

187
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,559
If it really doesn't work,

188
00:07:23,559 --> 00:07:25,279
we can go find the remaining employees

189
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:26,239
and have them run around.

190
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,399
That's also a way out.

191
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,799
Let's give it a try,

192
00:07:34,679 --> 00:07:35,359
okay?

193
00:07:42,119 --> 00:07:42,720
Okay.

194
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,200
Then,

195
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,079
let's give it our best shot.

196
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:48,839
Okay.

197
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,000
I know what to do.

198
00:07:52,679 --> 00:07:54,160
The investment prospectus we sent over,

199
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:54,839
have you read it?

200
00:07:56,119 --> 00:07:57,720
Could you please repeat that?

201
00:07:59,359 --> 00:08:00,040
Thank you.

202
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,359
How are things on your end?

203
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:06,480
Try this one.

204
00:08:06,799 --> 00:08:07,559
Call this number.

205
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:09,519
Hello, Mr. Zhang.

206
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,079
The proposal President Gu mentioned last time,

207
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,559
what do you think of it?

208
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,399
Understood.

209
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:15,200
Okay.

210
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:15,760
I'll follow up on it.

211
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,559
I checked.

212
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:18,839
The transplant surgery followed all procedures.

213
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:19,920
There were no issues.

214
00:08:20,239 --> 00:08:21,160
That's strange.

215
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,600
Why is Gu Tiancheng

216
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,480
looking for the heart donor?

217
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,320
Look at you.

218
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,399
You can never tie your tie properly.

219
00:08:31,839 --> 00:08:33,760
You have to look your best for Auntie today.

220
00:08:34,359 --> 00:08:35,440
Looking at you this closely,

221
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,159
you're not bad looking.

222
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,479
But why is it that whenever I see you,

223
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,359
I get so annoyed?

224
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,159
I also checked

225
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,760
the post-transplant interview records.

226
00:08:47,239 --> 00:08:48,719
It says that after the surgery,

227
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:50,320
there were drastic changes

228
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,000
in his behavior and personality.

229
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,080
Could it be...

230
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,760
Right now, our only hope

231
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:05,919
is this old auntie.

232
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:08,119
What?

233
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,479
This old auntie?

234
00:09:10,719 --> 00:09:11,960
Don't underestimate this old auntie.

235
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:12,919
Her background

236
00:09:13,239 --> 00:09:14,599
is definitely something you wouldn't expect.

237
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,840
What kind of background could an old auntie have?

238
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,239
Even though she looks quite old,

239
00:09:20,479 --> 00:09:21,239
she is actually

240
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,960
a very famous investor.

241
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,840
This old auntie?

242
00:09:27,359 --> 00:09:29,479
I'd believe it if you said she dances in the square.

243
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,080
But an investor?

244
00:09:31,119 --> 00:09:32,559
If she were really like you said,

245
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,359
she wouldn't have so many assets to her name.

246
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,960
This Auntie Zhang opened a

247
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,200
very humble porridge shop.

248
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,520
So people call her Porridge Granny.

249
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:39,919
What you need to pay more attention to

250
00:09:39,919 --> 00:09:41,559
is that her son has a level-two intellectual disability.

251
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,479
He is always with her,

252
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:43,159
never leaving her side.

253
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:44,559
So when you meet her,

254
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,599
you must be careful

255
00:09:45,599 --> 00:09:46,919
about how you speak to her.

256
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:47,919
Here.

257
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,239
Auntie,

258
00:09:54,479 --> 00:09:55,000
we would like...

259
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,479
We don't have it.

260
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,320
We'd like to order two bowls of red bean porridge.

261
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,159
Here,

262
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:01,000
we don't have the investment you want.

263
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:01,880
Leave.

264
00:10:09,239 --> 00:10:09,760
Auntie.

265
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,400
This matter...

266
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,400
...concerns the livelihoods of 4,500 people.

267
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:14,960
Please have some mercy.

268
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,000
Just take a look at this document.

269
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,640
The moment you bend over...

270
00:10:18,799 --> 00:10:20,119
...I know what kind of crap you'll pull.

271
00:10:20,479 --> 00:10:21,119
Stop nagging.

272
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,080
Get out.

273
00:10:22,359 --> 00:10:23,200
Hurry up and leave. Go.

274
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,559
Please reconsider.

275
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:25,080
You're here.

276
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:25,919
Come, come.

277
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:26,960
Have a seat.

278
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,479
Auntie Zhang.

279
00:10:27,479 --> 00:10:28,119
Come on in.

280
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:28,840
What would you like to eat?

281
00:10:29,479 --> 00:10:30,080
The usual.

282
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,039
The same old things.

283
00:10:31,599 --> 00:10:32,119
Auntie.

284
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:34,640
Auntie.

285
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:35,280
The usual.

286
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,200
This company is my father's...

287
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,159
...life's work.

288
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,559
Even if you try to kick us out today...

289
00:10:38,719 --> 00:10:39,599
...we're staying right here.

290
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:40,880
We have nowhere else to go.

291
00:10:42,359 --> 00:10:42,960
Kid.

292
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,359
Do you even know what having nowhere to go means?

293
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:46,440
Get out.

294
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:47,840
You two.

295
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,239
Kick them out.

296
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,200
Move.

297
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,000
Auntie.

298
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,440
Auntie, please take another look.

299
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:53,359
Don't touch me.

300
00:10:53,599 --> 00:10:54,440
Auntie, just take one look.

301
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,440
Whose stomach is growling?

302
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,799
Is it yours?

303
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,840
I should have waited a bit longer...

304
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,239
...to talk about the investment.

305
00:11:16,559 --> 00:11:17,359
Yeah.

306
00:11:17,359 --> 00:11:18,679
I haven't eaten all day either.

307
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,440
The porridge from that shop just now...

308
00:11:24,239 --> 00:11:26,039
...smelled so familiar.

309
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,840
It smelled exactly like my childhood.

310
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:30,280
Did you like eating porridge as a kid?

311
00:11:32,119 --> 00:11:33,039
When I was little...

312
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,760
...my dad would often bring back some...

313
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,599
...red bean porridge.

314
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:38,359
It smelled so good.

315
00:11:49,239 --> 00:11:50,440
Feimanchi.

316
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:52,440
Auntie.

317
00:11:52,799 --> 00:11:53,239
Auntie.

318
00:11:53,239 --> 00:11:53,960
Please take another look.

319
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:54,520
Don't touch me.

320
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,000
Auntie, just take one look.

321
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,440
Gu Tiancheng.

322
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,239
Gu.

323
00:12:01,719 --> 00:12:03,080
Then the remaining wrap-up work...

324
00:12:03,159 --> 00:12:04,119
...will be left to Old Hu.

325
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:06,960
Nelson.

326
00:12:09,599 --> 00:12:10,520
Long time no see.

327
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,000
You haven't been looking too well lately.

328
00:12:15,719 --> 00:12:17,440
Why don't you use your company's skincare products...

329
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,520
...to do some treatments?

330
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,719
It seems doing business...

331
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,479
...is harder than collecting debts.

332
00:12:24,239 --> 00:12:25,039
It's actually not that bad.

333
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,359
Thanks for your concern.

334
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,280
President Gu.

335
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,919
According to our agreement...

336
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:30,960
...if today...

337
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,679
...you still haven't produced the new product...

338
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,960
...it's time to repay the investment, right?

339
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,320
What?

340
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,559
You're still not ready?

341
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:39,960
That's right.

342
00:12:41,119 --> 00:12:41,919
I'm not ready yet.

343
00:12:45,239 --> 00:12:46,039
This is...

344
00:12:46,039 --> 00:12:46,840
...the new product project...

345
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,239
...transfer contract to Rosenmoss.

346
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:52,760
President Gu.

347
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,640
President Gu.

348
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,679
Are you still not going to sign?

349
00:13:00,559 --> 00:13:01,280
How about this?

350
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,320
Sign or beg for mercy.

351
00:13:04,239 --> 00:13:05,119
Pick one.

352
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,039
We...

353
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:09,280
...aren't unreasonable people.

354
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,080
Maybe if you beg us...

355
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:13,640
...we might change our minds.

356
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:54,239
President Gu.

357
00:13:56,799 --> 00:13:57,599
Auntie Zhang is here.

358
00:14:03,159 --> 00:14:03,760
Auntie Zhang.

359
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,400
Why are you here?

360
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:06,719
Tell me.

361
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,200
How much does he owe you?

362
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,359
Jiaqi.

363
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,400
The situation of your company,

364
00:14:31,599 --> 00:14:32,599
my investment advisor

365
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,559
has already reported to me in detail.

366
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,000
As for me,

367
00:14:36,599 --> 00:14:37,599
I have also decided

368
00:14:38,679 --> 00:14:40,159
to switch to a new investment field

369
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,080
and give it a try.

370
00:14:43,159 --> 00:14:44,320
I don't know how to express

371
00:14:44,799 --> 00:14:45,599
our gratitude.

372
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:48,200
Is there anything else?

373
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:50,479
If there's nothing else,

374
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:52,280
then let's settle the debts.

375
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:54,280
Why did that old woman suddenly step in

376
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,039
to help Gu Tiancheng?

377
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,320
How should I know?

378
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,640
Why are you losing your temper with me?

379
00:14:59,479 --> 00:15:01,000
Then have the people in the company act quickly.

380
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,359
Make sure to find out why Ms. Zhang

381
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:03,320
is helping Feimanchi.

382
00:15:03,919 --> 00:15:04,719
Come,

383
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,400
try our porridge.

384
00:15:10,559 --> 00:15:11,679
Careful not to break it.

385
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:12,479
Auntie,

386
00:15:13,359 --> 00:15:15,000
actually, even now I haven't figured out

387
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:16,640
why you suddenly agreed to help me.

388
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:19,840
If I had known

389
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,039
you were from Feimanchi,

390
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,760
I wouldn't have kicked you out yesterday.

391
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,559
Look at you, child.

392
00:15:24,799 --> 00:15:26,119
You came looking for investment.

393
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:27,520
Why didn't you

394
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:29,440
introduce yourself when you came in?

395
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,080
I just didn't have time to say it

396
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,880
before the person next to you...

397
00:15:36,119 --> 00:15:37,000
It's my fault.

398
00:15:37,359 --> 00:15:38,000
I

399
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,679
know you love our porridge.

400
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:40,880
I also know

401
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:41,880
that every time you eat porridge,

402
00:15:42,239 --> 00:15:43,919
you add lots and lots of sugar,

403
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,599
just like my Xiaojun.

404
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,520
That's enough, that's enough.

405
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,840
Your dad told me.

406
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:49,520
Here.

407
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:51,799
Auntie, you...

408
00:15:52,679 --> 00:15:53,640
You know my dad?

409
00:15:53,679 --> 00:15:54,760
Of course I do.

410
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:55,760
Your dad

411
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,919
was a regular at our shop.

412
00:15:58,520 --> 00:15:59,320
Back then,

413
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:01,000
when my husband passed away,

414
00:16:01,479 --> 00:16:02,640
just a widow and an orphan,

415
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,039
we had no one to rely on.

416
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,440
I thought to myself then,

417
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:07,479
I know how to make porridge,

418
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,159
so let's open a porridge shop.

419
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,960
We worked hard for a year

420
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,280
and finally made some money,

421
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,039
only to have it scammed away.

422
00:16:16,159 --> 00:16:17,200
For my whole life,

423
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:19,280
I will always be grateful to your dad.

424
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,320
If it weren't for your dad,

425
00:16:22,679 --> 00:16:23,679
Xiaojun and I

426
00:16:24,679 --> 00:16:26,520
might not have survived to this day.

427
00:16:29,919 --> 00:16:30,440
Auntie,

428
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,840
the past is in the past.

429
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:34,719
Look,

430
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,760
isn't everything fine now?

431
00:16:37,599 --> 00:16:38,679
Xiaojun is doing well too.

432
00:16:39,239 --> 00:16:39,919
Yes.

433
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:42,520
That's why,

434
00:16:43,039 --> 00:16:44,159
from that day on,

435
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,000
I told myself

436
00:16:46,679 --> 00:16:48,400
I must work hard to live on.

437
00:16:49,039 --> 00:16:50,239
I have to work hard

438
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,919
so I can repay your dad's help in the future.

439
00:16:55,559 --> 00:16:56,440
And now,

440
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,719
it's time to repay that kindness.

441
00:16:59,799 --> 00:17:01,119
So you

442
00:17:01,119 --> 00:17:02,640
must also work hard

443
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:04,439
to become an entrepreneur

444
00:17:04,439 --> 00:17:06,119
just like your dad.

445
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:12,359
Don't worry, Auntie.

446
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,040
I definitely will.

447
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:16,680
I've checked.

448
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,280
Many products in this store

449
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:19,800
have this tropical fish pattern.

450
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:21,760
It seems to be their main theme.

451
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,520
When I was at their storefront,

452
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:24,719
I thought it was a

453
00:17:24,719 --> 00:17:25,280
pet and plant market.

454
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,000
Okay, okay, okay.

455
00:17:26,199 --> 00:17:27,239
Enough about the tropical fish.

456
00:17:27,239 --> 00:17:27,800
Get to the point.

457
00:17:29,479 --> 00:17:31,199
Du Zheng bought a watch from them.

458
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,040
Du Zheng bought one?

459
00:17:35,959 --> 00:17:36,680
The key is,

460
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:38,599
the owner actually remembers.

461
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,800
He said Du Zheng asked him to wrap it nicely,

462
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:42,599
saying it was a gift for a friend.

463
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,319
In other words,

464
00:17:46,599 --> 00:17:47,719
at the crime scene,

465
00:17:48,359 --> 00:17:49,719
Du Zheng and that friend of his

466
00:17:49,719 --> 00:17:50,719
appeared at the same time.

467
00:17:54,079 --> 00:17:54,760
What do you mean?

468
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,119
Nothing much.

469
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,959
What does Gu Tiancheng mean?

470
00:18:07,719 --> 00:18:08,599
Feng Ziang.

471
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,119
Hope you've been well.

472
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,239
You're finally here.

473
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,760
I've been waiting for you.

474
00:18:15,079 --> 00:18:16,160
Tan Feng escaped from the hospital.

475
00:18:16,319 --> 00:18:16,800
What did you say?

476
00:18:17,439 --> 00:18:18,640
Didn't I tell you to watch him closely?

477
00:18:19,079 --> 00:18:19,839
He was there just a moment ago.

478
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:21,560
He's not very mobile right now,

479
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:22,640
so he couldn't have gone far.

480
00:18:23,079 --> 00:18:24,319
I will definitely find him.

481
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:32,400
Is that so?

482
00:18:32,839 --> 00:18:34,479
I thought you didn't want to see me.

483
00:18:34,719 --> 00:18:35,560
How could that be?

484
00:18:38,479 --> 00:18:39,400
Let's talk somewhere else.

485
00:18:52,359 --> 00:18:53,560
Why did you run away from the hospital?

486
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,239
The police told me

487
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:57,880
that once I get out of the hospital,

488
00:18:58,599 --> 00:18:59,599
they would

489
00:19:00,119 --> 00:19:02,199
arrest me again for gambling.

490
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:04,119
I really don't want to go back to prison.

491
00:19:04,359 --> 00:19:05,280
It's torture.

492
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:06,719
Feng Ziang,

493
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,079
you know so much about me.

494
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,319
Did you send someone

495
00:19:10,839 --> 00:19:11,800
to watch me at the hospital?

496
00:19:12,199 --> 00:19:13,479
You're being paranoid again.

497
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:14,719
Let me tell you,

498
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,359
stop being so suspicious all the time.

499
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,000
Don't treat me like a fool.

500
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,719
My every move

501
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,199
is under your surveillance.

502
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,479
Then why did you suddenly come back now?

503
00:19:27,479 --> 00:19:28,560
Didn't we have a deal?

504
00:19:29,239 --> 00:19:30,560
You find a kidney for my wife,

505
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:32,439
and get my kid into the best school.

506
00:19:32,839 --> 00:19:34,040
Why aren't you keeping your promise?

507
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,319
I wasn't the one who told you to gamble.

508
00:19:35,319 --> 00:19:36,800
Nor did I tell the police to arrest you.

509
00:19:37,719 --> 00:19:38,800
How could you be so stupid?

510
00:19:39,439 --> 00:19:40,520
The police are watching so closely right now.

511
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:41,719
How could I possibly make cash transactions?

512
00:19:42,359 --> 00:19:43,280
You're always right.

513
00:19:43,719 --> 00:19:44,439
Let me tell you,

514
00:19:44,839 --> 00:19:46,040
my wife is dying.

515
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,400
Just wait a little longer.

516
00:19:49,439 --> 00:19:50,359
Lay low for now.

517
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:51,000
Wait?

518
00:19:51,119 --> 00:19:52,000
I can't wait anymore.

519
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,319
I want you to do it right now.

520
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,479
Suit yourself.

521
00:19:55,839 --> 00:19:57,400
This case was only

522
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:58,760
closed because of my dad's death.

523
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,599
My dad traded his life for this.

524
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,439
Besides, this case

525
00:20:03,439 --> 00:20:04,359
has no physical evidence at all.

526
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,680
Do you think the police would investigate

527
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,880
a closed case?

528
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,800
How can you be so naive?

529
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,319
No wonder you can only hide.

530
00:20:15,479 --> 00:20:16,199
You...

531
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,920
can't do anything right.

532
00:20:25,079 --> 00:20:26,400
Du Zheng already knows everything.

533
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,800
The substandard materials incident...

534
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,640
We did it.

535
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:29,439
He knows all about it.

536
00:20:29,959 --> 00:20:30,920
If you wake him up,

537
00:20:31,199 --> 00:20:32,239
we'll all go to prison.

538
00:20:33,359 --> 00:20:34,079
Big things,

539
00:20:34,719 --> 00:20:36,119
I believe I can't accomplish.

540
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:37,839
But such a small thing,

541
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,199
I believe I can definitely do it.

542
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,839
You secretly recorded me behind my back?

543
00:20:50,719 --> 00:20:52,479
I have to leave myself a way out.

544
00:20:52,959 --> 00:20:53,520
Besides,

545
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,160
I didn't secretly record you.

546
00:20:55,719 --> 00:20:56,920
I don't even know what happened.

547
00:20:57,599 --> 00:20:58,280
Maybe

548
00:20:58,760 --> 00:20:59,839
God took pity on me

549
00:21:00,599 --> 00:21:01,839
and gave me a gift.

550
00:21:02,319 --> 00:21:03,079
Feng Ziang,

551
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:04,520
does this count as evidence?

552
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:06,719
I'll take it to the police station tomorrow.

553
00:21:07,239 --> 00:21:08,160
Let's see if the police

554
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:09,760
will reopen the investigation.

555
00:21:13,479 --> 00:21:14,199
What's going on?

556
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,000
When I bought my car back then,

557
00:21:17,599 --> 00:21:19,079
they gave me a dashcam.

558
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,239
I didn't expect it to be so useful.

559
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:24,439
A dashcam?

560
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:25,400
Yeah.

561
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,119
The dashcam

562
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:28,400
is at my place.

563
00:21:30,439 --> 00:21:31,920
You fulfill your promise right now,

564
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,319
or else

565
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,280
I'll go to the police station immediately.
